<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-08T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8682: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-08T17:00:00+09:00">July 8, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 8—6:29 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>185. We are informed by the Foreign Office that official Japanese reports
                            from Peiping indicate that prospects are favorable for settlement of the
                            brush which took place this morning near Peiping between Japanese and
                            Chinese troops. It was stated at the Foreign Office that <pb facs="0411" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/> “our military people seem to believe that
                            the firing by Chinese troops which started the incident was not
                            premeditated.”</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>